Over 2, 000 aliens were so far registered by the Nigerian Immigration Service (NIS), Jigawa State command in accordance  with presidential directive. The public relations officer of the command, Bala Abdullahi Adamu, revealed this while fielding questions from newsmen on the ongoing nationwide registration of immigrants in Nigeria He said, following the presidential directive for immigration service to register all the immigrants living in Nigeria, the state command swung into action without any delay. The PRO noted that, according to the presidential directive six month was declared as an  amnesty period during which every immigrant would be registered free of charge without considering having or not having any valid documents to enter Nigeria. He also expressed satisfaction on the aliens’ turnouts and cooperation given to the exercise, adding that after the six months  amnesty  period the exercise would continue according to the expected  presidential directives. Speaking to Journalists at the immigration  service headquarters, Dutse, the secretary of the Association of Niger Citizens Living in Jigawa State, Malam Tanimu Isyaku Dutse, said his association was given all necessary cooperation for the exercise through making official arrangement for transporting their members from across all 27 local governments of the state to the command headquarters for the registration.